        java.lang.OutOfMemoryError - Indicates insufficient memory for increasing the queue's capacity. Note: An attempt to increase the capacity beyond Integer.MAX_VALUE will cause the queue to fail with an arithmetic overflow.

      • clone

        public LinkedQueue<E> clone()
        Generate a copy of this queue.
        Overrides:
        clone in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        The return value is a copy of this queue. Subsequent changes to the copy will not affect the original, nor vice versa. Note that the return value must be type cast to an LinkedQueue before it can be used.
